  "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
  "body": "Currently, the PV binder matches claims with the exact access modes on the volume and claim.  For example, a GCEPD with RWO+ROX will bind only to a claim that requests RWO+ROX.\n\nMatching should be loosened to allow users to request fewer modes but possibly get more than they asked for.  A user can request RWO in a claim but get a GCEPD with RWO+ROX.\n\nGetting more than requested follows storage, which matches on at least the amount requested (5Gi) but could be more (the volume actually has 10Gi).\n",
